### **Introduction**

This project was assigned as part of the Digital Literacy course to help students understand the importance of using digital tools effectively and responsibly. As a Student Digital Ambassador, the goal of this project was to spread awareness among peers about digital platforms, communication, and online safety.

Through this project, I explored various tools such as Canva, GitHub, LinkedIn, and Google Forms. I also learned how to maintain a professional online presence and communicate effectively in a digital environment. Each task focused on a different aspect of digital literacy, including creating visual content, building a digital portfolio, exploring online platforms, practicing email etiquette, and understanding cybercrime.

Overall, this project helped me improve my digital knowledge and skills, which will be useful in both my academic and professional journey.

---

### **Task-1**

In Task 1, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. The infographic was designed to explain important concepts in a simple and visually appealing way. It included topics such as the meaning of digital literacy, safe internet practices, useful digital tools for students, and maintaining a professional online presence.

While creating the infographic, I focused on keeping the design clean and easy to understand. I used headings, icons, and simple points to make the content more attractive. One interesting part was learning how to present information visually without making it too crowded.

Initially, I found it slightly difficult to choose the right design and layout, but after some practice, I was able to create a neat and informative infographic. This task helped me understand the importance of visual communication.

---

### **Task-2**

In Task 2, I created my student digital portfolio by setting up and updating my profiles on GitHub and LinkedIn. GitHub is a platform used for managing and sharing projects, while LinkedIn is a professional networking platform used to connect with others and explore career opportunities.

On GitHub, I updated my profile by adding my name, bio, and basic details. On LinkedIn, I completed my education section and created a simple professional profile.

This task helped me understand the importance of having a professional digital presence. Over the next four years, I plan to regularly update my profiles, add projects, and connect with people in my field. This will help me build a strong digital identity and improve my career opportunities.

---

### **Task-3**

In Task 3, I explored coding and collaboration platforms. I created an account on a coding platform and completed a beginner-level problem, which helped me understand how these platforms are used for practice and skill development.

I also created a Google Form as a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz. The form included five questions related to digital safety and awareness. I linked the form with a Google Sheet to collect responses.

This task helped me learn how online tools can be used for both learning and collaboration. Coding platforms improve problem-solving skills, while Google Forms can be used for quizzes and surveys. Overall, this task gave me practical experience with useful academic tools.

---

### **Task-4**

In Task 4, I learned about professional communication through email writing and social media etiquette. I wrote two formal emails—one requesting an extension for an assignment and another expressing interest in an internship opportunity. This helped me understand how to write clear and professional emails.

I also created a checklist of do’s and don’ts for social media usage. This helped me understand the importance of maintaining a responsible and positive online presence.

A situation where poor communication can cause problems is when a student sends an email without a subject line or uses informal language. This can create a bad impression. Using proper email etiquette can help avoid such issues.

---

### **Task-5**

In Task 5, I researched cybercrime, specifically UPI payment fraud. I learned how fraudsters trick people into sending money through fake links or payment requests. These scams are very common and can happen quickly if users are not careful.

One thing that surprised me was how easily people can fall into such traps due to lack of awareness. Many users do not verify payment requests before accepting them.

This task helped me understand the importance of online safety. As a result, one habit I will change is always verifying payment requests and avoiding unknown links. I will also ensure that my personal and financial information remains secure.

---

### **Conclusion**

This project was a valuable learning experience that helped me understand different aspects of digital literacy. From creating an infographic to building a professional portfolio and learning about cyber safety, each task improved my skills.

It also made me more aware of responsible online behavior and the importance of maintaining a professional digital presence. The knowledge gained from this project will be helpful in my academic life and future career.

Overall, this project has increased my confidence in using digital tools effectively and responsibly.

